entries.femaleVariant: And they had salmon tartare, from an actual salmon farm - can you imagine how much that must've cost?
Next time you should take me with you. It's been ages since I was in Tokyo.
Oh, and I also saw Hashima Island. They built this beautiful colombarium inside a disused mine.
Really took my breath away. S'just too bad all the niches were already reserved.
They keep saying they wanna go back to Okinawa, they don't know how much time they have left...
Well, the colombarium in Night City also has its charm... And they'd be close, too...
True... I just hope I won't have to be makin' that decision anytime soon...
